description: Number of ordered factorizations of n with 3 levels of parentheses.
comments: a(n) depends only on prime signature of n (cf. A025487). So a(24) = a(375) since 24 = 2^3*3 and 375 = 3*5^3 both have prime signature (3,1).The Dirichlet inverse is given by A050356, turning all but the first element of A050356 negative. - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 15 2010
author: _Christian G. Bower_, Oct 15 1999
